text: Salt Lake County is a county located in the U.S. state of Utah. As of the 2020 census, the population was 1,185,238, making it the most populous county in Utah. Its county seat and largest city is Salt Lake City, the state capital. The county was created in 1850. ==References== Category:Utah counties Category:19th-century establishments in Utah Category:1850 establishments in the United States
